cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CR 

The paper deals with object detection using knowledge distillation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a novel method for fine-grained feature imitation, which involves estimating locations and imitating the teacher model on them, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper evaluates the method on various object detection benchmarks, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) as object detection is often used in security applications.
